1
00:00:00,834 --> 00:00:04,792
Tab 1
1
I walked in and saw around 25 people sitting here

2
00:00:05,250 --> 00:00:07,626
They were sitting here, spread out here and there

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:14,584
The place was clean and the lights were on

4
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:19,125
And the floor was covered with carpet

5
00:00:19,459 --> 00:00:22,209
They had prepared it to be a hall and a mosque

6
00:00:23,792 --> 00:00:26,042
When you first enter, at the beginning, at the reception

7
00:00:26,959 --> 00:00:28,667
They record your statements and so on

8
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,876
You sit here until another person comes

9
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:35,584
Who then distributes us into the prison cells

10
00:00:36,834 --> 00:00:39,709
The hall was organized and clean, and the lights were on

11
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:42,709
And people were sitting here

12
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:46,709
Interviewer: Did you enter with your shoes on or without them?

13
00:00:46,792 --> 00:00:50,475
No, when we reached the stairs, they made us take off our shoes

14
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:51,934
Interviewer: You mean everyone took off their shoes?

15
00:00:51,959 --> 00:00:52,959
Yes, everyone took off their shoes

16
00:00:53,083 --> 00:00:55,918
Interviewer: You said it was covered with carpet

17
00:00:55,918 --> 00:00:59,375
Yes, with striped red carpet

18
00:01:00,918 --> 00:01:03,667
Interviewer: So was this hall open like it is now?

19
00:01:03,709 --> 00:01:05,834
Or did it have partitions and divisions?

20
00:01:05,834 --> 00:01:06,959
No, it had dividers

21
00:01:07,190 --> 00:01:08,709
They had divided the place with a curtain

22
00:01:08,751 --> 00:01:09,834
This part wasn’t visible

23
00:01:10,584 --> 00:01:14,209
Interviewer: Do you remember the exact color of the curtain?

24
00:01:15,792 --> 00:01:19,876
It was indigo, fading into black almost

25
00:01:21,542 --> 00:01:24,042
Interviewer: Was there any sponge mattress to sit on?

26
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:27,042
No, there was no sponge mattress, we sat on the floor

27
00:01:27,626 --> 00:01:33,125
Interviewer: You said this was a temporary detention center, or a mosque?
Witness: Yes

28
00:01:33,167 --> 00:01:35,626
Interviewer: How did you know it was a mosque?

29
00:01:35,792 --> 00:01:37,542
There was a prayer rug

30
00:01:38,209 --> 00:01:39,375
There was a prayer rug here

31
00:01:40,459 --> 00:01:43,209
And people were sitting, and when prayer time came

32
00:01:43,792 --> 00:01:48,083
It was covered with carpets specific to mosques

33
00:01:49,083 --> 00:01:50,876
So it was obvious it was a mosque

34
00:01:51,834 --> 00:01:53,918
Interviewer: Did you pray here in this place?

35
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:55,167
Yes, I prayed here

36
00:01:55,292 --> 00:01:59,709
Interviewer: During your entire stay here, two days and one night

37
00:01:59,751 --> 00:02:01,584
Were all your prayers here?

38
00:02:04,542 --> 00:02:06,375
No, they took us down to pray here

39
00:02:07,083 --> 00:02:10,083
Interviewer: Was the imam from among you prisoners?

40
00:02:10,125 --> 00:02:11,667
Or was he one of their men?

41
00:02:11,709 --> 00:02:12,709
No, he was one of their men

42
00:02:12,959 --> 00:02:16,083
Interviewer: Can you describe to me how you prayed?

43
00:02:16,125 --> 00:02:17,417
And what direction the qibla was?

44
00:02:17,417 --> 00:02:18,876
The qibla was in this direction

45
00:02:19,417 --> 00:02:21,209
The qibla this way, and the rows were like this

46
00:02:22,042 --> 00:02:23,042
The qibla was like this

47
00:02:23,083 --> 00:02:24,250
Interviewer: So it was tilted at an angle?

48
00:02:24,292 --> 00:02:26,959
Yes, it was tilted at an angle, not straight ahead

49
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:33,083
Interviewer: Don’t you remember how many prayer rows there were when you prayed?

50
00:02:34,459 --> 00:02:37,167
When we entered, the 25 people

51
00:02:38,417 --> 00:02:39,792
After the call to prayer we prayed

52
00:02:40,709 --> 00:02:43,918
They would bring some of the others but not all of them

53
00:02:44,751 --> 00:02:46,584
The sick and others prayed upstairs

54
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:48,918
And whoever couldn’t go down because of torture

55
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:51,918
Stayed upstairs and prayed there

56
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:53,667
At dawn prayer time

57
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:57,834
You had to wake up an hour before the prayer

58
00:02:58,292 --> 00:03:00,959
Wait your turn to go to the toilet and then do <i>wudu</i> [ablution]

59
00:03:00,959 --> 00:03:02,250
Finish <i>wudu</i> then come to pray

60
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:07,334
Interviewer: Do you mean that all the time you were in prison you prayed here?

61
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:08,375
Yes in this place

62
00:03:08,751 --> 00:03:09,918
Interviewer: I will ask you a question

63
00:03:09,959 --> 00:03:12,626
Interviewer: Did they force you to perform the obligatory prayer? Witness: Yes

64
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:15,209
Interviewer: Did they force you to perform the voluntary prayer?

65
00:03:15,209 --> 00:03:19,042
Meaning, did they force you to perform it or was it up to you?

66
00:03:19,083 --> 00:03:22,667
No, it was up to you, but when you first entered you had to show you did the voluntary prayers

67
00:03:22,667 --> 00:03:25,167
Yes, you had to pray the ones before and after

68
00:03:26,042 --> 00:03:30,000
And he would lead us in their special <i>duaa</i> [supplication] that could last up to 15 minutes

69
00:03:31,125 --> 00:03:33,417
Interviewer: What do you mean by <i>duaa</i>? Witness: Their special supplication prayer

70
00:03:34,209 --> 00:03:37,375
“O God, grant us victory over those who are hostile to us”... and so on

71
00:03:37,751 --> 00:03:40,334
Interviewer: Was this during group prayer? Witness: Yes in every prayer

72
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:42,417
Interviewer: Was it the imam who made the supplication? Witness: Yes him

73
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:45,959
The reason was that they didn’t want any prisoner to be the imam

74
00:03:46,542 --> 00:03:49,083
They wanted one of their own to lead the prayer and the <i>duaa</i>

75
00:03:49,334 --> 00:03:53,751
Interviewer: So this supplication that you called <i>duaa</i>

76
00:03:53,834 --> 00:03:57,125
Do you remember specific words from it?

77
00:03:57,125 --> 00:04:00,834
Yes, like, “O God grant us victory... O God deal with so-and-so”

78
00:04:00,876 --> 00:04:06,083
Yes, “O God deal with America... O God deal with the apostates”

79
00:04:06,959 --> 00:04:08,918
And all of those words

80
00:04:08,959 --> 00:04:10,959
Interviewer: Was this supplication repeated at every prayer?

81
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,209
Yes, it was repeated at every prayer

82
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:13,667
Interviewer: And were you required to respond behind him?

83
00:04:13,667 --> 00:04:16,834
Yes we were required to, and you had to raise your hands and say Amen loudly

84
00:04:17,626 --> 00:04:21,918
Interviewer: Describe to me how the prayer was, and the supplication

85
00:04:22,042 --> 00:04:24,209
I stood here and the imam stood there

86
00:04:24,667 --> 00:04:26,500
And he raised his hands and made supplication

87
00:04:26,751 --> 00:04:28,667
And you said, O God Amen

88
00:04:28,751 --> 00:04:32,500
While some of them stood behind the windows

89
00:04:32,542 --> 00:04:34,292
Looking through to see who among us didn’t raise his hands

90
00:04:34,334 --> 00:04:36,167
And whoever didn’t say Amen, they held him accountable

91
00:04:36,508 --> 00:04:37,959
Interviewer: Was this at every prayer?

92
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Yes, at every prayer

93
00:04:39,042 --> 00:04:41,792
Interviewer: Was the <i>duaa</i> at every prayer? Witness: Yes

94
00:04:42,334 --> 00:04:46,083
Interviewer: Okay, if someone didn’t raise his hands and say Amen

95
00:04:46,125 --> 00:04:48,542
Was he held accountable, or did everyone raise their hands?

96
00:04:48,542 --> 00:04:50,334
You had to raise your hands, you were forced to

97
00:04:50,334 --> 00:04:52,417
Like I told you, one stood here and another there

98
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,500
Watching us while we prayed

99
00:04:54,709 --> 00:04:57,209
And whether someone wasn’t supplicating sincerely

100
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,459
Interviewer: The imam was the one who made the supplication

101
00:05:00,792 --> 00:05:02,459
And you behind him said Amen

102
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:08,918
Do you remember if he cried? Or was he pretending to cry? Or was he not crying?

103
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:15,709
He was pretending to be devout and that he was supplicating from the bottom of his heart

104
00:05:16,751 --> 00:05:19,250
Sometimes his voice went down and sometimes he raised it

105
00:05:20,584 --> 00:05:22,334
Interviewer: Was the imam from Mosul?

106
00:05:22,334 --> 00:05:25,459
Or was he from the clans, or from other nationalities?

107
00:05:25,751 --> 00:05:26,959
No, he was from the clans

108
00:05:28,292 --> 00:05:30,292
Interviewer: Do you mean he was not from Mosul?

109
00:05:30,292 --> 00:05:31,709
No, he didn’t speak with the Moslawi accent

110
00:05:32,042 --> 00:05:35,250
Interviewer: In this prison, were there no people from Mosul?
Witness: Yes, there were

111
00:05:35,292 --> 00:05:36,626
Interviewer: As ISIS guards?

112
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:39,292
Do you mean ISIS members? No, there were none

113
00:05:39,292 --> 00:05:43,083
None of them spoke in our Moslawi accent

114
00:05:44,042 --> 00:05:46,500
But there were people from Mosul among them

115
00:05:46,542 --> 00:05:48,709
But not here, I did not see them here in this hall

116
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:51,042
Interviewer: How many prayers did you pray in this hall?

117
00:05:51,792 --> 00:05:55,584
When I came, I did not pray the noon prayer because I was late

118
00:05:56,042 --> 00:05:58,918
I prayed the afternoon, sunset, and night prayers

119
00:05:59,792 --> 00:06:02,459
And the dawn prayer, then we left before the noon prayer

120
00:06:02,918 --> 00:06:04,584
Interviewer: Do you mean four prayers?
Witness: Yes

121
00:06:04,626 --> 00:06:06,918
Interviewer: Did you perform all four prayers in congregation?

122
00:06:06,918 --> 00:06:07,959
Yes, and the <i>duaa</i> [supplication] of qunoot

123
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,584
Interviewer: Was it the same imam?
Witness: No, it changed

124
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:13,709
There were two or three of them

125
00:06:14,542 --> 00:06:15,709
Each one led us in prayer

126
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:19,959
Interviewer: Were there Qurans or chairs in this hall?

127
00:06:20,292 --> 00:06:23,125
There were no chairs, but there were Qurans

128
00:06:24,209 --> 00:06:28,334
Interviewer: Were there cameras filming you?

129
00:06:28,334 --> 00:06:31,209
And was there a flag of theirs?

130
00:06:31,334 --> 00:06:33,167
I did not notice if there were cameras

131
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:37,334
But the flags were outside

132
00:06:40,334 --> 00:06:44,709
And I think there was an ISIS flag here

133
00:06:45,083 --> 00:06:46,792
Interviewer: You mean the banner?
Witness: Yes, their banner

134
00:06:46,876 --> 00:06:50,751
Interviewer: Was there a screen where they showed their videos?

135
00:06:50,792 --> 00:06:52,667
No, I didn’t see one here

136
00:06:53,709 --> 00:06:55,125
Interviewer: You didn’t see one?
Witness: No, I didn’t
